[2.130877, "o", "Usage:\r\n  helix run [--agent codex|claude] [--review-every N] [--max-cycles N] [--no-auto-align] [--no-auto-review] [--summary] [--dry-run]\r\n  helix frame [--agent codex|claude] [scope]\r\n  helix build [--agent codex|claude] [selector]\r\n  helix check [--agent codex|claude] [scope]\r\n  helix align [--agent codex|claude] [scope]\r\n  helix backfill [--agent codex|claude] [scope]\r\n  helix design [--agent codex|claude] [--rounds N] [scope]\r\n  helix polish [--agent codex|claude] [--rounds N] [scope]\r\n  helix start [helix run options...]\r\n  helix stop\r\n  helix status [--json]\r\n  helix next\r\n  helix review [--agent codex|claude] [scope]\r\n  helix experiment [--agent codex|claude] [--close] [issue-id|goal]\r\n  helix evolve [--agent codex|claude] [--scope S] [--artifact ID] [--from source] \"requirement\"\r\n  helix triage \"Title\" [--type task|epic|bug|chore] [ddx bead create options...]\r\n  ddx bead <command> [args...]\r\n  helix help\r\n\r\nCommands:\r\n  run         Loop over ready HELIX work, then check whether to continue\r\n  start       Launch helix run as a background process (PID file written)\r\n  stop        Kill the background helix run cleanly\r\n  frame       Create or refine product vision, PRD, and feature specs\r\n  build       Run one bounded implementation pass\r\n  check       Run the bounded HELIX queue-health check\r\n  align       Run reconcile-alignment for a scope (default: repo)\r\n  backfill    Run documentation backfill for a scope (default: repo)\r\n  design      Create a comprehensive design document through iterative refinement\r\n  polish      Refine issues before implementation (dedup, coverage, criteria)\r\n  next        Show recommended next issue\r\n  review      Fresh-eyes review of recent work\r\n  experiment  Run one experiment iteration for metric-driven optimization\r\n  evolve      Thread a new requirement through the artifact stack\r\n  commit      Commit with HELIX format, run build gate, push, close issue\r\n  triage      Create a bead via ddx bead create\r\n\r\nOptions:\r\n  --agent           Agent to use: codex or claude (default: codex)\r\n  --claude          Shorthand for --agent claude\r\n  --codex           Shorthand for --agent codex\r\n  --model           Model to use (e.g., claude-sonnet-4-6, gpt-5.4)\r\n  --effort          Reasoning effort: low, medium, high, max (defaults vary by action)\r\n  --review-every    Run alignment every N completed implementation cycles\r\n  --max-cycles      Stop after N completed implementation cycles\r\n  --no-auto-align   Do not auto-run alignment when check returns ALIGN\r\n  --no-auto-review  Do not run fresh-eyes review after each implementation\r\n  --review-threshold N  Skip review for changes below N lines (default: 100)\r\n  --review-agent    Use a different agent for reviews (default: adversarial alternate)\r\n  --smart-model     Model for reasoning-heavy stages (frame, design, align, review)\r\n  --cheap-model     Model for mechanical stages (build, polish, check)\r\n  --dry-run         Print the agent command instead of executing it\r\n  --quiet, -q       Suppress progress output (command echo, prompt sizes)\r\n  --summary, -s     Concise output with log-file line pointers (implies --quiet)\r\n\r\nEnvironment:\r\n  HELIX_AGENT          Default primary agent (codex or claude)\r\n  HELIX_ALT_AGENT      Alternate agent for adversarial rotation (auto-detected)\r\n  HELIX_AGENT_TIMEOUT  Agent timeout in seconds (default: 2700)\r\n  HELIX_SMART_MODEL    Model for reasoning stages (default: opus / gpt-5.4)\r\n  HELIX_CHEAP_MODEL    Model for mechanical stages (default: sonnet / gpt-5.4-mini)\r\n  HELIX_LIBRARY_ROOT   Override the library root that contains workflows/\r\n  HELIX_TRACKER_DIR    Override the tracker directory (default: .helix/)\r\n\r\nAdversarial rotation:\r\n  Primary agent (frame, design, evolve, align, review) uses the smart model.\r\n  Alternate agent (build, polish, check) uses the cheap model.\r\n  This ensures different models review each other's work.\r\n\r\nLogs:\r\n  Session logs are written to .helix-logs/helix-YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS.log\r\n  in the project root. All stderr output is captured for post-hoc inspection.\r\n\r\nNotes:\r\n  Codex runs as .\r\n"]
